[3] India (Maharashtra)
Date: Fri 4 Jun 2010
Source: Yahoo News [summ. & edited]
<http://in.news.yahoo.com/48/20100604/804/tnl-civic-body-hospitals-gear-up-to-figh.html>


People are suffering from dengue and malaria, especially in
Pimpri-Chinchwad. Dr Milind Jawale, medical officer, national health
programmes in Pimpri-Chinchwad, said ... dengue fever was recorded
among 679 patients last year [2009] and till May this year [2010]
there have been 34 cases.

Dr Sadashiv Patole, in-charge of the insect control department at the
PMC [Pune Municipal Corporation] has started 'gate meetings' at
cooperative societies to prevent dengue and malaria. He said there
were 170 cases of dengue in the city last year [2009]. This year till
April [2010], there have been 14 cases of dengue. "As part of our
preparedness campaign, we have put up banners in the city and tried to
inform citizens via the electronic media to refrain from storing water
for more than 5 days at their homes," he said.

Doctors and hospital administrators have also had their hands full at
Sassoon Hospital. "We saw 191 cases of dengue (10 deaths) [in 2009],"
... said Dr PS Pawar, medical superintendent.

The count:
Pimpri (till May [2010]) dengue: 34
Pune (till April [2010]) dengue: 14

--
