[6] Brazil (Rio Grande do Sul)
Date: Fri 4 Jun 2010
Source: Zero Hora [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://zerohora.clicrbs.com.br/zerohora/jsp/default.jsp?uf=1&local=1§ion=Geral&newsID=a2926809.xml>


Dengue cases in Porto Alegre cause neighboring municipalities to
intensify the fight against mosquitoes. Canoas, Viamao, and Alvorada
take preventive action to avert risk of the disease. A least [these] 3
neighboring municipalities will increase care with dengue, after
confirmation of 2 cases of the disease in the capital. In Canoas, an
emergency survey of vector mosquito breeding sites will be done in the
Niteroi and Rio Branco neighborhoods. Starting next Wednesday [9 Jun
2010], 80 [health] agents will visit residences, commercial
establishments and vacant land in search of _Aedes aegypti_ larvae.
The supervisor of the fight against epidemics of the Prefecture,
Patricia Valentim, emphasized that care should be redoubled.

In Viamao, the army will help the prefecture in the fight against
dengue; 25 agents will be contracted as an emergency. In Alvorada,
health surveillance plans to return to the region bordering Porto
Alegre. The municipality was visited by [health] officers and soldiers
in May [2010]. The state government decided to intensify the work to
combat dengue in all of Rio Grande do Sul, with special attention to
the metropolitan region.

--
