[7] Brazil (Minas Gerais)
Date: Fri 4 Jun 2010
Source: Montes Claros [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://montesclaros.com/noticias.asp?codigo=49088>


So far this year [2010], dengue has killed 38 people in Minas Gerais,
with 6 in the capital, according to the totals of the state
Secretariat of Health. Last year [2009], the disease killed 24 people
in the state, so there has been an increase of 58 percent in just 5
months this year [2010]. Another 59 hemorrhagic-type deaths from the
disease are under investigation by the Secretariat of Health. In Belo
Horizonte there are 16 deaths suspected for this most serious form of
the disease [DHF]. In Montes Claros 2 deaths of suspected dengue were
recorded. For one of these, a 21-year-old student, dengue was
laboratory confirmed but not yet confirmed as DHF. Of the current
dengue deaths in Minas Gerais, 22 were dengue with complications and
16 were DHF.

--
