[8] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Fri 4 Jun 2010
Source: Gazeta de Ribeirao [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.gazetaderibeirao.com.br/conteudo/mostra_noticia.asp?noticia=1690425&area=92020&authent=046F03662B0650BDD608FDBBBFE9B6>


The confirmed dengue cases in Ribeirao Preto from [1] Jan [2010] to
the day before yesterday [2 Jun 2010], increased by 48 percent over
the total of confirmed cases of the disease in the last 10 years.
According to the municipal Secretariat of Health, from 2001-2009, 16
553 people were diagnosed with the disease. This year [2010], ill
individuals now total 24 523.

The residents of the Campos Eliseos, in the Zona Norte, and the Parque
Ribeirao neighborhoods have the greatest [number] of victims of the
_Aedes aegypti_ mosquito, the vector of the disease [virus]. The 1st
[locale] totals 1729 [dengue cases] and the 2nd 1727.

Last month [May 2010], when the number of cases fell almost by half in
relation to April -- there were 3933 confirmed cases versus 7828 in
the previous month, or 50 percent -- the 2 neighborhoods remained on
the top of the dengue ranking in the city: Parque Ribeirao reported
233 new infected individuals and Campos Eliseos, 228.

According to the municipal Secretary of Health, Stenio Miranda
Correia, the Secretariat began to register a fall of 50-60 percent per
week in notifications of [dengue] cases. "What we have to do now is
work preventively to so that we do not have so many cases next year
[2011], " said the secretary.

Last week [week of 24 May 2010], a task force formed by the City
collected 25.5 tons of recyclable materials, possible breeding sites
for the dengue mosquito vector, in the neighborhoods of Ribeirao Park,
Maria Graca, and Progresso and Marchesi gardens. The sweep found 101
foci of mosquito breeding in 87 homes, but there were 121 property
owners who refused the entry of agents during the sweep.

The reappearance of dengue [virus] type 2 in Ribeirao Preto could
cause a new epidemic in the coming year [2011], which now worries the
municipal Secretariat of Health. According to Maria Luiza Santa Maria,
director of the Division of Health Surveillance, the last time this
virus type circulated intensively in the city was in 2001. The virus
is divided into 4 types -- this year [2010] type 1 predominates and is
considered the most explosive and it caused the epidemic considered
the worst in all history of the city.

A total of 24 523 dengue cases were registered in Ribeirao Preto this
year [2010].

[Byline: Gabriela Yamada]

--
