[9] Brazil (Rio de Janeiro)
Date: Fri 28 May 2010
Source: O Sao Goncalo [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.osaogoncalo.com.br/geral/2010/5/28/12898/17+pessoas+já+morreram+de+dengue+no+rio++++>


The state Secretariat [of Health] announced that up to Thursday (26
May 2010), 17 people died of dengue in the entire state of Rio de
Janeiro. In Sao Goncalo, 6 deaths were recorded. Another report shows
that 13 154 suspected cases of the disease were recorded up to May
2010. In the same period in 2009, 9566 [dengue] cases were reported.

The municipalities with the highest number of cases are Tangua, Sao
Goncalo, Macae, Itaborai Itaperuna, Casimiro de Abreu, with Rio de
Janeiro in 7th place.

